# Java formatting

Place `else` and `else if` on their own line, directly below the closing brace:

```java
// ✅ GOOD
if (condition) {
    doSomething();
}
else {
    doSomethingElse();
}

// ❌ BAD
if (condition) {
    doSomething();
} else {
    doSomethingElse();
}
```

## Object equality

Use `equals` to compare objects. Reserve `==` for primitives and null checks.

```java
// ✅ GOOD
if (statement.equals(NO_OPERATION)) {
    return;
}

// ❌ BAD
if (statement == NO_OPERATION) {
    return;
}
```
